title.narrative: Women Empowered for Leadership and Development (WELD)

description.narrative: (Sierra Leone): With FY 2017 funds, the Women Empowered for Leadership and Development (WELD) program is focused on improving women's skill, interest and knowledge to run for public office and also strengthening the demand for women politicians by political parties. The program will focus on strengthening successful women candidates' contribution to policy-making and development...WELD will improve the capacity of female aspirants and elected women candidates through training and mentorship. WELD will partner a local NGO which specializes in organizing workshops in leadership, public speaking, fundraising, and mobilizing constituencies. This will build the skills of female aspirants to mount more issue based campaigns with the hopes of being successful in their political pursuits. With a new government in place, the women who have received our training would be able to ensure that women's voices are heard in all aspects of policy-making through all levels of government.
